cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the detection of lung nodules in computed tomography (CT) images using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). The use of data augmentation and ensemble learning also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) focus. The proposed sampling strategy and cascaded prediction method may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.MS). Finally, the use of 3D CNNs for classification suggests a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
